description: Phased development for the construction of between ten and twenty storey mixed use development comprising: Part A - Purpose Built Student Accommodation (PBSA) with a ground floor flexible hub (Sui Generis); and Part B - Office floorspace with associated ground floor uses (Use Class E(g)(i)), together with related outdoor amenity spaces, landscaping, public realm improvements, cycle and DDA vehicle parking, refuse storage and ancillary and enabling works
decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interest of proper planning. | The development (but excluding site survey and ground investigation works, utility diversions, demolition, site clearance works, remediation of any contamination, preliminary infrastructure works, site preparation works, any archaeological and investigations and erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding) shall not commence until details of the phasing of the construction of the development hereby approved, and the extent of each phase, has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details shall include drawings that illustrate the following:
(a) building(s) and other structures included within each phase of development; and
b) the scope of the public realm works and landscaping within each phase.

The development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details, unless alternative phasing details are submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. For the avoidance of any doubt, the phases identified on the approved plan shall also comprise the phases within the development for the purposes of calculating and paying Community Infrastructure Levy which may include an 'early works' phase containing no chargeable floorspace.

Reason: To ensure appropriate sequencing of development in order to provide the timely delivery of each block of the development, areas of public realm and landscaping relative to each phase of development; car parking and cycle storage facilities necessary to serve the relevant phase of development; and to ensure that the extent of development is acceptable from construction management, transport planning and environmental pollution perspectives. | Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, details of materials and finishes to be used for all external building surfaces and samples shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority for each individual phase, prior to commencement (excluding initial site clearance and ground works) of the relevant phase. Each phase of the development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter.

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings in accordance with Policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19).

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, details of hard and soft landscaping, boundary treatments and outdoor furniture for that particular phase shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to occupation of that phase of the development. The approved details shall be implemented and retained as such thereafter.

Reason: To ensure appropriate hard and soft landscaping, boundary treatments and outdoor furniture in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area and public realm, in accordance with Policies D3, D4 and D8 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the development hereby approved, a Landscape Management Plan (which shall include a programme for its implementation) for the relevant phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The landscaping shall be carried out and thereafter managed in accordance with the approved details for the lifetime of the development.

Reason: To ensure appropriately landscaped amenity space and public realm, in accordance with Policies D3, D4 and D8 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the development hereby approved, details of construction, specification and maintenance of the green roofs, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority for the relevant phase. The green roofs shall be implemented and managed in accordance with these approved details for the lifetime of the development.
Reason: To improve the natural environment and biodiversity, in accordance with Policies G5 and G6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 5.11 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).

| Prior to commencement of the relevant phase of the development hereby approved (but excluding site survey and ground investigation works, utility diversions, demolition, site clearance works, remediation of any contamination, preliminary infrastructure works, site preparation works, any archaeological and investigations and erection of temporary boundary fencing or hoarding), a Biodiversity Gain Plan (which shall include a programme for its implementation) for that particular phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter.
Reason: To ensure that the biodiversity gain objective is met, in accordance with Schedule 7A of the Town and Country Planning Act (1990) and Policy G6 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the development hereby approved, the greening measures to achieve an Urban Greening Factor (UGF) score of 0.4 for that phase shall be fully implemented. The implemented greening measures shall be retained and adequately maintained thereafter.

Reason: To improve the natural environment and biodiversity, in accordance with Policies G5 and G6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies 5.10 and 5.11 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).

| The roof of the buildings shall not be used for any purpose other than as a means of escape in emergency or for maintenance of the buildings unless indicated as external amenity space in the approved drawings listed under condition 2.

Reason: To safeguard the amenities of future occupiers, neighbouring properties and the area generally, in accordance with Policy 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the development hereby approved, details of the hours of use of the external amenity spaces in respect of that phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The external amenity spaces shall operate in accordance with the approved details for the lifetime of the development.

Reason: To safeguard the amenities of future occupiers, neighbouring properties and the area generally in accordance with Policies D6 and D14 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 3.5 and 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19).

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, prior to occupation of the purpose-built student accommodation (PBSA) hereby approved, a Purpose-built Student Accommodation Management Plan (including a pick-up and drop-off strategy), shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The PBSA shall be managed in accordance with the approved details for the lifetime of the PBSA.

Reason: To safeguard the amenities of future occupiers, neighbouring properties and the area generally in accordance with Policies D6 and D14 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 3.5 and 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19).
| The total number of occupants within the purpose-built student accommodation (PBSA) shall not exceed one (1) person per bedroom or studio.

Reason: To prevent over occupancy, in the interest of living conditions of future occupiers, in accordance with Policy D6 and H15 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 3.5 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).

| 11 per cent of the approved purpose-built student accommodation (PBSA) rooms shall be designed and constructed to meet Part M volume 1 of the Building Regulations, Building Regulation requirement M4(3).
Reason: To provide inclusive student accommodation, in accordance with Policy D7 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the development hereby approved, the passenger lifts identified in the approved drawings listed in condition 2 shall be installed for the relevant phase and made fully operational. The installed passenger lifts shall be permanently retained and maintained in good working order thereafter.
Reason: To provide adequate access to all floors, in accordance with Policy D7 of the London Plan (2021).

| The refuse storage for each phase of the development as identified in the approved drawings listed under condition 2 shall be brought into use prior to first occupation of that phase and retained permanently for the lifetime of the development.
Reason: To ensure adequate refuse storage, in accordance with Policy SI 7 of the London Plan (2021).

| The cycle storage for each individual phase of the development identified in the approved drawings listed under condition 2 shall be brought into use prior to first occupation of the relevant phase and retained permanently for the lifetime of the development.
Reason: To ensure adequate cycle storage, in accordance with Policy T6 of the London Plan (2021).

| Notwithstanding the provisions of The Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 (as amended) (or any order revoking and re-enacting that Order with or without modification), or the provisions of The Town and Country Planning (Use Classes) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2020, the development hereby approved shall only be used as purpose-built student accommodation (PBSA) (Sui Generis) and office floorspace (Use Class E(g)(i)) as identified in the approved drawings listed in condition 2, together with ancillary uses, and for no other purpose, unless otherwise agreed in writing with the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.

Reason: To control the nature of the use and safeguard the amenities of the area generally, in accordance with Policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013), Policy D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft new Local Plan (Regulation 19).

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, a Delivery and Servicing Plan for the relevant phase of the development shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to occupation of that individual phase of the development. The development shall operate in strict accordance with the approved details in perpetuity.

Reason: To ensure adequate highway safety and safeguard the amenities of future occupiers, neighbouring properties and the area generally, in accordance with Policies T3, T4, T7 and D14 of the London Plan (2021), Policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the development hereby approved, a Car Parking Design and Management Plan, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority for the relevant phase. The car parking shall be provided and managed in accordance with the approved details for the lifetime of the development.
Reason: To ensure adequate highway safety and parking, in accordance with Policies T4 and T6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 6.13 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the development hereby approved, all car parking spaces for the relevant phase identified in approved drawing number UXB-CWA-XX-00-DR-A-2002 Rev P011 shall be equipped with active electric vehicle charging provision. This provision shall be permanently retained thereafter and shall only be altered for maintenance or upgrades.
Reason: To provide adequate electric car charging provision, in accordance with Policy T6 of the London Plan (2021).
| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents:
(a) a PBSA Travel Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to occupation of the PBSA hereby permitted; and
(b) an Office Travel Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to occupation of the office development hereby permitted.

Each Travel Plan shall be prepared in accordance with the Transport for London Travel Plan Guidance and Ealing's Sustainable Transport for New Development SPD in use at the time of its preparation. Each phase of the development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved Travel Plans in respect of that phase.

Reason: To encourage sustainable transport and reduce traffic and congestion, in accordance with Policies T1, T2, T4, T5 and T6 of the London Plan (2021) and Ealing's SPD 'Sustainable Transport for New Development'.

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, a Construction Management Plan shall be submitted for each phase of the development and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to commencement of the relevant phase of the development. The development shall not be implemented other than in accordance with the approved details. Details shall include:
a) control measures for:
- noise and vibration (according to Approved CoP BS 5228-1 and -2:2009+A1:2014),
- dust (according to Supplementary Planning Guidance by the GLA (2014) for The Control of Dust and Emissions during Construction and Demolition),
- lighting ('Guidance Note 01/20 For The Reduction Of Obtrusive Light' by the Institution   of Lighting Professionals),
- delivery locations,
- hours of work and all associated activities audible beyond the site boundary restricted to 0800-1800hrs Mondays to Fridays and 0800 -1300 Saturdays (except no work on public holidays),
- neighbour liaison, notifications to interested parties and
- public display of contact details including accessible phone numbers for persons responsible for the site works for the duration of the works
b) details related to:
- pre-construction highway survey,
- traffic management,

- construction lorry route from the main distributor roads and the number of constructions related vehicles, which would be travelling to the application site.  A drawing showing signing for the construction vehicles is also required,
- key dates of various stages and all the emergency contacts during construction,
- abnormal load delivery vehicle routes and dates of these deliveries, and
- swept path envelopes for construction lorries, HGV's and crane vehicles.

Reason: To ensure that the amenity of occupiers of neighbouring properties and the area generally is not adversely affected by noise, vibration, dust, lighting or other emissions from the site, in accordance with Policies D14, SI 1, SI 2, T4 and T7 of the London Plan (2021), Policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013), Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Regulation 19), the NPPF (2023) and SPG10 Noise and Vibration. | Prior to commencement of any construction works for each phase of the development (excluding initial site clearance and ground works), a noise assessment report in respect of that phase shall be submitted to the Council for approval in writing, of external noise sources including transport/ industrial/ commercial/ cultural uses and their noise levels occurring at the site during most of the year, ie. Measured during school and work weekdays, in accordance with internal noise limits specified in BS8233:2014, and including the aircraft noise data in Section 6, SPG10 (worst mode aircraft 1-day noise contour (57dB). Details shall include the sound insulation of the building envelope including glazing specifications (laboratory tested including frames, seals and any integral ventilators, approved in accordance with BS EN ISO 10140-2:2010) and of acoustically attenuated mechanical ventilation and cooling as necessary (with air intake from the cleanest aspect of the building and details of self-noise). Best practicable mitigation measures shall also be implemented, as necessary, in external amenity spaces to achieve criteria of BS8233:2014. The approved details shall be implemented prior to occupation of the relevant phase of development and thereafter be permanently retained.

Reason: In the interests of the living conditions of the future occupiers of the site, in accordance with Policies D6 and D14 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies 3.5 and 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).

| Prior to the installation, details shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in writing, of plant/ machinery/ equipment/ducting/air in- and outlets/ mechanical installations and their external rating noise level (LAr,Tr), together with mitigation measures as appropriate for each phase of the development.
